content:
Enable users to select a checkbox by adding the Checkbox element to your OmniScript. For example, map the user's yes/no answer to a true/false field in a record.

Drag a Checkbox element from the Build panel onto the canvas.
In the Properties panel, give the element a name in the Name field.
In Field Label, enter a label visible to the user.
(Optional) Select Default Value to enable the checkbox by default. The value is true or false in the Data JSON.
(Optional) For additional properties, see Common OmniScript Element Properties Definitions.

Checkbox Properties
Checkbox properties are configurable from the Properties panel when you select a Checkbox element. With the Checkbox element, enable users to select a checkbox in your OmniScript.
title: OmniScripts Checkbox Element
